actions and workflow transitions need deterministic server validation before the model can change session state.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:37:3. Durable orchestration: prompts, structured outputs, retries, and model selection need to be coordinated with persistent session data and job records.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:51:The durable model should include job records, segment records, asset metadata, and an event log that can reconstruct session progress after interruption.\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:61:- `repositories/`: database access for sessions, events, jobs, and assets\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:71:- Session\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:72:- Workflow stage\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:74:- Selected genre\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:75:- Selected tone\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:76:- Story brief\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:77:- Pitch batch and selected pitch\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:78:- Character batch and selected character sheet\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:79:- Beat sheet\ndocs/architecture-overview.md:103:Story setup preferences such as word count, runtime, and chapter count are planning hints rather than hard limits. The system should use them to guide prompts, estimates, and editing suggestions without forcing exact compliance at the expense of story quality or bedtime tone.\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:179:.session-group__header p,\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:180:.session-card__timestamp,\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:181:.session-summary-card span,\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:459:.session-card-list,\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:897:.genre-selection-grid {\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:901:.tone-selection-grid {\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:905:.genre-selection-card__facts {\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:911:.tone-selection-card__facts {\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:917:.genre-selection-card__facts div,\nfrontend/src/styles/index.css:918:.tone-selection-card__facts div {\nfrontend/src/styles/index.