sonlines:124:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_68\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Implemented the FastAPI scaffold in commit `72e6065`. The backend now uses an app-factory layout with settings, services, models, DB placeholders, unversioned and versioned routers, `GET /health`, `GET /api/v1/health`, and a preserved `GET /api/hello` compatibility route. Key files are [main.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/main.py), [config.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/settings/config.py), [router.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/api/router.py), and [test_health.py](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/tests/test_health.py).\\n\\nVerification passed with backend pytest, `compileall`, live local startup plus `curl` checks, Docker Compose startup with the new `/health` healthcheck, and the existing browser smoke spec. The required reviewer summary was written last to [03-fastapi-scaffold.summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/prompts/03-fastapi-scaffold.summary.md). Current intentional limit: database wiring is still a scaffold and reports `not-configured` until later prompts.\"}}\nfrontend/package.json:7:    \"dev\": \"vite\",\nfrontend/package.json:8:    \"build\": \"tsc -b && vite build\",\nfrontend/package.json:12:    \"preview\": \"vite preview\",\nfrontend/package.json:13:    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\nfrontend/package.json:28:    \"@vitejs/plugin-react\": \"^6.0.1\",\nfrontend/package.json:37:    \"vite\": \"^8.0.1\",\nfrontend/package.json:38:    \"vitest\": \"^4.1.2\"\n./prompts/13-storage-abstraction-and-buckets.yolopilot.jsonlines:16:{\"color\": \"cyan\", \"emoji\": \"\\ud83d\\udee0\\ufe0f\", \"event_type\": \"Command Finished\", \"message\": \"completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc 'rg --files'\", \"raw_event\": {\"item\": {\"aggregated_output\": \"secrets.example.yaml\\nprompts/00-project-charter.codex.jsonlines\\nprompts/36-conversation-memory-summaries.md\\nprompts/11-postgres-schema-and-migrations.summary.